post_text: Out at Lake Dallas Middle School, your tax dollars are hard at work making way for big changes. You will notice work is going on above ground and underground to make way for a new addition. Utilities on the site are being relocated from the footprint of the future addition. post_text: Gov. Greg Abbott has issued an executive order requiring Texans to wear masks that cover the nose and mouth when in public spaces in counties with 20 or more positive COVID-19 cases, with some exceptions. The requirement is in effect when 6 feet of social distancing is not possible. Based on county health data, this requirement is now in effect in Denton County.

Greg Abbott has issued an executive order requiring Texans to wear masks that cover the nose and mouth when in public spaces in counties with 20 or more positive COVID-19 cases, with some exceptions. The requirement is in effect when 6 feet of social distancing is not possible. Based on county health data, this requirement is now in effect in Denton County.

post_text: At Lake Dallas Middle School demolition of site and existing building features continues as we prepare for the building additions. We have been fortunate with clear weather and optimum working conditions on all of our project sites. Let’s hope it continues! At LDMS, right-of-way work at the new entry is moving along and paving will begin a week ahead of schedule. Site utility work has begun with the installation of storm sewer improvements. As you can see, there is a lot of work to be done, but our construction crew is taking it step-by-step! #FalconProud #BuildingTogether

post_text: We are happy to report our bond program project at Lake Dallas Middle School is moving ahead safely and swiftly. The City of Lake Dallas has released our building permit for the site. Concrete removal is complete despite the rainy weather over Memorial Day weekend. The construction crew is proceeding with grading operations to level the site. Utility installations will begin soon followed by paving areas south of the school adjacent to E. Hundley Road. #FalconProud #BuildingTogether

post_text:
🎓💚Senior spotlight💚🎓 Aubrey Thomas

Aubrey has overcome a lot in her 18 years. We moved from Florida to Texas her Senior year. As usual, she overcame the obstacles this school year has thrown at her. Nursing was always her dream, but she found fuel for her creativity in welding and choir. She was a part of the welding team that competed at the Fort Worth Stockyards show and placed second. Aubrey is following her heart to Tulsa Welding School to obtain her Associates of Occupational Studies in Welding Technology. Aubrey's ultimate goal, as she gains valuable experience, is to start her own welding/welding inspection business. Reach for the stars "babygirl" and HE will lead the way!!

We are so very proud of you Aubrey. Hard work pays off! 💚🙏🌹🎓🏁

post_text:
LDHS Senior Spotlight: Devin Stepp

Devin is a 13 year Lake Dallas graduate. He's enjoyed jumping with Falcon Flyers and then playing trombone in the band.

He sings with The Millennial Choirs and Orchestra and had the privilege to sing at the Tabernacle on Temple Square in SLC and Carnegie Hall in NYC. He has the gift of perfect pitch, but he won't tell you that.

He's a fun, loving, helpful, caring, & thoughtful young man. He has always been a sensitive & empathic young man and has NO tolerance for abuse of any kind. He's gotten in "trouble" a few times by telling female friends when her boyfriend isn't treating her well. He works well with those with "disabilities" and does what he can to include them in whatever the activity.

He's pursuing a career in Automotive Engineering and is a talented low voltage technician... if you know our family neither of those should be a surprise.

LDHS Senior Spotlight: Daniel Harger
I want to congratulate my son, Daniel Harger on his graduation.

We have been through some ups and downs but I couldn't be prouder of you! You are l your father's son when it comes to never meeting a stranger.

Daniel is a 7.5 year Falcon. We moved to Corinth in the middle of his 5th grade year. He was part of the LDMS football team for 7th and 8th grade, then again in 9th and 10th. He was part of the football film crew, theater tech crew in 10th grade and his love of science drew him to the science club.

👩🏼🎓💚 Senior Spotlight 💚👩🏼🎓
Congratulations to Morgan Yount! You have grown into such an amazing young woman and I am so proud of you!
Morgan has been her Class treasurer all four years of high school, a member of French National Honor Society, Radio Club, and played volleyball up thru her sophomore year. Her love for art, history and languages is what inspired her to major in Anthropology as she starts her college career at The University of Texas in Austin this fall. Words can never express how much I love you and how excited I am to see what the future holds for you!
Love, Mom

post_text:
This is Clarissa Melody McKinley. Most know her as Melody or Mel. She was often seen behind the lens of a camera as a member of the yearbook staff. Melody pushed and challenged herself to conquer her naturally shy and quiet personality by interviewing fellow students and asking to take their pictures. She was a member of STUCO for three years, French Honor Society and the Renaissance club.

Her hard work, competitive spirit and dedication earned her scholarships to Texas Tech University where she will study Construction Engineering. Her ultimate goal is to blow up building, bridges or anything else that’s allowed.

When I asked her for a quote that represents her today, she replied, “She do be graduating tho.” ~ Author Unknown

post_text:
Senior Spotlight!✨💫 🎓
Congratulations to my little sister Shelly Maldonado. Even though it hasn’t been an easy road for you, you pushed through thick and thin and now here you are!

Shelly joined the Lake Dallas Falcon family only 4 years ago as a freshman in high school. During her time here, she enjoyed her Spanish and Dance classes, and being part of the CIS group.
Outside school she spent time practicing Aikido and attending her church youth group. She’s planning to attend El Centro College in Dallas in its nursing program.

Our family is so proud of you and can’t wait to see the woman you’re becoming.
#class2020 #seniorspotlight

post_text:
💚 Senior Spotlight 💚
Class of 2020
Congratulations to Olivia Greer, a 13 year LDISD Falcon!
You are kind, funny, beautiful (inside and out), and encouraging.
Your smile is infectious.

Olivia was involved in TAFE, Ready Set Teach, Student Council, Special Olympics and Drill Team during high school. She has been heavily involved with youth group and youth choir at our church for the past 7 years.

She will be attending Oklahoma State University 🧡🖤 in the fall majoring in Elementary Education. Go Pokes!

Liv, we are so proud of you!
With much love,
Mom, Dad and Delaney

post_text:
💚Senior Spotlight 💚
Class of 2020
Congratulations Martaesia Fisher..
I am so proud of you and the young lady you have became.
I know this year didn't end the way you expected but you handled it like a champ and finished strong.

Martaesia has been on the honor roll since elementary school. She participated in praise dance and choir at church and also was apart of clean up Lewisville and volunteered at the nursing home with the youth at our church.

Martaesia was a office aid and a basketball manager, she also ran cross country.

Martaesia has always been interested in computers, she will be attending Prairie View A&M majoring in computer engineering and minoring in computer science.

I am extremely proud of you and look forward to the next step in your journey. I will always be your biggest cheerleader!

I love you,
Mom 💖

post_text:
🦠Senior spotlight🦠
Class of 2020🎓
Congratulations to our 13 year Lake Dallas Falcon, Josephine Elliott!
Jo has had a love of sports from a very early age. No matter what ball she picked up, the game came naturally. She played volleyball, basketball, track, and tennis through out middle school. When she got to high school she concentrated on her favorite sport, basketball. She was a four year letterman and led her team to the Regional tournament her senior year. Her accomplishments include: 4x academic all-district, 1st team all-district, district MVP, 2nd team all area, 1st team Denton county, and was team captain since her sophomore year.

Josephine will play basketball next year at the University of Texas at Tyler and major in kinesiology.

We are so proud of you Jo and can’t wait to see you on the court next year! We know you’ll do great things, beautiful girl!

Love, Mom, Dad, Allyson, Jorja, and Chase

💥💥SENIOR SPOTLIGHT💥💥
Congratulations to Taylor Varin, a 13 year Lake Dallas Falcon🎉
Taylor has such a joyful heart.🙏🏻 She is funny, thoughtful and so carefree. 💕

Taylor has loved playing basketball and volleyball in MS. She played Volleyball her freshman year, ran Varsity track her Junior year. Taylor played Varsity soccer all four years in HS and was captain her Junior and Senior year.🌟

Taylor received academic all district all four years.💫 She was Vice President of her class Freshman through Junior year.✨

Taylor will be attending the University of North Texas to major in business and minor in Music.🦅

Taylor,
We love your passion for life and your excitement for what’s ahead. We know you will do great things!
All our Love,
Mom, Dad & Christian

post_text:
Kennedy Dugan is our 2020 Senior and 10 year Lake Dallas Falcon!! 💚👩🏼🎓

Kennedy was born at a very early age and for a brief moment held the record as the youngest human on Earth.

She is a four year letterman of the Lady Falcon Varsity Softball. During her high school career, Kennedy’s honors include: 2017, 18, 19 Academic All District, 2018 2nd Team All District, 2019 Honorable Mention All District and 2020 DFW Player to Watch before the cancellation of the softball season her senior year:(.

Kennedy will be attending NCTC studying Radiology.

We are proud of what you have accomplished your high school career and can’t wait to see what you can accomplish in the future! Happy Halloween! We love you, Mom and Dad

post_text:
Senior Spotlight – Christian Hernandez 🎓

Christian has been a Lake Dallas Falcon since the second grade. He has made countless friends throughout his years at LDISD. He is genuine and loving person, and a loyal friend.

Ever since he was young, Christian has always had a knack to strike up a conversation with people of any age. This skill will help him as he aims to pursue his dreams in a career in sales and advertising.

Christian has been passionate for the game of football since he was able to walk and he thoroughly enjoyed his days on the field as a LD Falcon. However, he has decided to decline a couple offers from small colleges to play at the next level and complete his college prerequisites at NCTC.

Christian we are so proud of you and we know your future is bright. Congratulations, we love you very much!
Love,
Mom, Dad and Ashlynn

Love,
Mom and Dad ￼

post_text:
LDHS Senior Spotlight – Kaleb Ledbetter

Kaleb Ledbetter is our intelligent, humble, kind hearted, and hardworking son. Despite the obstacles, we are so excited to congratulate him on his high school graduation. In school, Kaleb has always had a natural understanding of math. He’s enjoyed and excelled in his (many!!) math, engineering, physics, and computer science classes. In the fall, Kaleb will be continuing his interests in these areas at Texas A&M University in the engineering program.

He has always been very passionate about soccer, beginning at 4 years old. He especially enjoyed his time playing with his friends these past 4 years and is proud of the accomplishments the Lake Dallas soccer team was able to achieve. Of course, we all wonder what could have been for this team had it not been for this nasty virus.

Though 2020 didn’t end the way we would have liked for him and his classmates, it doesn’t change how proud we are of him and how excited we are for what his life holds for him in the future.

We love you Kaleb! - Mom, Dad, Audrey, and Jacob

post_text:
Senior Spotlight - Audrey Fink

As the parents of Audrey Fink we are excited to have the opportunity to offer her a few thoughts upon graduating:
It is now time, Audrey, to say goodbye to the chapter at LDISD as part of your journey to the next educational challenge. The road to graduating from high school is never smooth and is paved with lots of bumps and challenges. We noticed that you persevered and were tenacious in setting and meeting goals that included dual credit courses, working two jobs, caring for family, and all the while excelling at all your other classes. You, and you alone, earned that GPA! You are fortunate to have already decided your career goal of health care management with a degree in business. It is exciting that you are looking ahead and communicating with your new college roommate as well as wearing the Oklahoma State University sweatshirts. You are transitioning as you say goodbye. With your talents and dedication, the sky is the limit. Stay fierce and determined as your loving cheering squad in Denton is watching and applauding you.
Love,
Mom and Dad

LDHS Senior Spotlight - 🎓 👨🏼🎓

Antonio Banyaga is our creative, determined, and intelligent son who has grown into such a wonderful young man. He loves academics and enjoyed being the president of the Science Club, a member of NHS, and volunteering in Student Council. Outside of school Antonio loves spending time making art 🎨, creating music 🎵, and hanging out with his friends. Antonio works hard to challenge himself and pushes himself to excel in the areas he is passionate about. Antonio will be graduating as the valedictorian of the LDHS class of 2020 💚. He will be majoring in Chemical Engineering at the University of Texas at Austin 🤘🏽🧡. We are so proud of Antonio and all his many accomplishments 🌟!
We love you and can’t wait to see what your future holds 🎉!
Your biggest fans,
Mom, Dad, and Amelia

Senior Spotlight❤❤❤❤
Jaeden Holloway

This amazing creature has the heart of gold! She is caring and loving and would absolutely bend over backwards to help someone in need. She has a special place in her heart for special needs kiddos and plans to major in Special Ed and minor in ASL so that she can teach her future students to communicate when the words won't come. She intends on attending either Collin County or NCTC to get her prerequisites out of the way before transferring to a four year college in to be determined at a later date. She is the light that makes the darkness bright and the smile that makes the world spin! We definitely love you more than you could ever imagine!

Congratulations Class of 2020🎊🎓💚🎉
Senior Spotlight 🎓💚
Trey Bennett

We are so excited to congratulate our 13 year Lake Dallas Senior Trey Bennett. Trey has the biggest heart and would do anything to help someone. He has always been our family comedian, and has always enjoyed making people laugh. He is the best big brother and is very protective of his little sister & brother. Trey has been a student athletic trainer all four years of high school. He is also apart of the EMT program. Which has played a part in Trey determining his career path. Trey with attend NCTC where he will continue to build on his EMT certification and get his Paramedic certification. With his ultimate dream being to continue on in school to become an Athletic Trainer. We are so excited for his next adventure. He was made to do great things! We are so extremely proud of Trey!!!!

LDHS Senior Spotlight – Sarah Majecki

Sarah Majecki is our 13 Year Lake Dallas Senior! Words cannot described how proud we are on your graduation. Life has been tough on Sarah the last few years with her Dad's health issues and made her learn what is important in life a lot faster than most and for that we so grateful. She loves her family and relies on her faith to get through difficult times. Sarah is our beautiful, caring, kind and sassy girl. Sarah will attend NCTC in the fall to get her basics completed and then pursue a degree in dermatology. We love you to the moon and back and can't wait to see what the future holds for you!

post_text:
LDHS Senior Spotlight: Hunter McDaniel

Hunter McDaniel is our 2020 Senior! He is kind hearted, laid back, and funny. Hunter loves hunting, fishing, being outdoors and hanging out with his family and friends.

He also has tremendous love for the game of baseball, he was a 3rd year starter on the Varsity baseball team . Hunter has been playing baseball since he was 3 years old and has loved every minute of it. We have traveled many many miles over the years watching him play and although we are sad his High School season was cut short we are thankful for all of the memories and friends we have made along the way.

Hunter will be continuing his education and baseball career at Oklahoma Wesleyan University to major in Wildlife Management.

We are so proud of you Hunter!! We can't wait to see what Great things you do.
Love, Mom, Dad, Andrea & Cody

post_text:
LDHS Senior Spotlight: Aaron Martin

Your childhood has passed much too quickly for us. It seems like just 6 years ago we were in sunny Florida. We moved to Lake Dallas 6 years ago and I watched you grow into a young man. I watched an inexperienced football player become a beast but earned the respect of his team and peers. I watched a shy singer become a vocalist.(wish you would have stayed in choir). Your journey is just beginning and I can hardly wait to see what you accomplish next. The United States Navy will mold you into a leader and you will learn things beyond your dreams. Sky is the limit. We will always be here to support you and we’re so very excited to see what the future holds for each of you.

Life passes quickly, so be sure to enjoy all the little things. Whatever you do, bring glory to the one who made you.

Love,
Mom, Aerica Jordan, Andrew Martin, and Alexander Martin

LDHS Senior 2020 Spotlight: Jonah Webb

This is Jonah Webb. Not only is he a 13 year senior but he started out in the daycare at Corinth Elementary at four months old. For the Falcons he played football, basketball and baseball. He loves all sports but his favorite is baseball.

In high school he was the first group to participate in the welding program.

He loves to custom build furniture, rebuild/restore older vehicles, fish and hang out with his friends.

In the fall he plans to go to UT Tyler and major in mechanical engineering.

I could not be more proud of him.

LDHS Senior 2020 Spotlight – Abigail Kent

Abby is a 13 year senior. Abby we are so proud of everything you've accomplished! These past 4 years have been rough with multiple surgeries and everything else, but you've blazed through it like the amazing young woman you are! You don't know it, but you've paved a way for any student with a disability! You've been involved in it all! Theater, cheer, soccer, stuco (freshmen year), Renaissance club!

Girl, you never let anything stop you! And now you are graduating in the top 15% of your class! You are amazing, keep letting the world try and underestimate you, and keep showing them WHO you are!

post_text:
LDHS Senior 2020 Spotlight – Nicholas Love

🎉HUGE CONGRATULATIONS🎉to our LDHS Class of 2020 Graduating Senior - Nicholas Love‼️❤️👨🏼🎓🎉 Nick is our smart, funny & very talented Falcon Saxophonist.🎷🎶 He has been an active leader in the award-winning Lake Dallas Falcon Marching Band all four years, as well as Woodwind Captain & Section Leader both Jr & Sr years, and 1st chair alto sax (Wind Ensemble & Jazz1) for both Jr & Sr years. Nick was honored to play in the All Region Bands all 4 years, All Region Jazz for Jr & Sr years, Lone Star Youth Winds Orchestra in 2018/2019 season, and the Lone Star Ambassadors of Music 2018 European Tour. Nick made “1” Ratings for State solos & ensembles each of his first 3 years, and we're sure he’d achieve the same exceptional rating this year if Texas State Solo & Ensemble Contest wasn’t cancelled.😢

Nick has been accepted in to the College of Engineering at UNT. We are so very proud of all of Nick’s accomplishments, and we love his passion for Jazz‼️ We are really excited to see where the next chapter takes him.❤️ With so much love, Mom & Dad‼️

post_text:
LDHS Senior 2020 Spotlight – Skylar Billingsley

CONGRATULATIONS 🎉 🎓 to our Graduating Class of 2020 Senior -🌟Skylar Billingsley🌟. Skylar has attended LDISD since Kindergarten. She started cheer in 6th grade after making the switch from competitive gymnastics. She’s been apart of the LDHS cheer team all 4 Yrs of High School finishing as Co-Captain this year.

We are so proud of all of Skylar’s accomplishments including maintaining a 4.0 throughout High School and participating in various clubs including NHS, Student Council, BPA, Chess Club , Science Club, & Falcon Friends.

She is finishing in the top 20 of her graduating class and will be attending Suffolk University in Boston, MA majoring in Interior Design next year. She has been awarded the Deans scholarship and invited to the Honors program.

We can’t wait to see what all your future holds. We love you 💚

post_text:
LDHS Senior 2020 Spotlight – Holly Simpson

Holly Simpson is our 2020 Senior and 13 year Lake Dallas Falcon!! 💚👩🏼🎓 She is an amazing young lady and has a smile on her face all of the time! She is an intelligent, funny, God-fearing young lady with an infectious laugh!

Holly is a member of NHS, French NHS, Lady Falcon Varsity Softball, and is finishing as number 5 out of her entire graduating class.

During her high school career Holly has been active in PALS, Falcon Friends, Student Council, Renaissance Club, & CFA Leader Academy. Her softball honors include: 2017,18,19 Academic All-District, 2017,18,19 Academic All-State, and 2019 NFCA All-American Scholar Athlete. Senior season was cancelled:(.

On Friday, May 1, 2020, we celebrate School Lunch Hero Day! This is a special day of celebration to recognize school nutrition professionals and the difference they make every day!

Between preparing healthy meals for Texas students, adhering to strict nutrition standards, navigating student food allergies, and offering service with a smile, school nutrition professionals are true heroes.

And during this time of closure our Child Nutrition Staff has worked tirelessly to provide thousands of meals for our students. Thank you - you are our heroes!

LDHS Senior 2020 Spotlight – Maddie Vest

Maddie Vest is our Class of 2020 Senior and a 13 year LD student 💚. We are so proud of all of Maddie’s accomplishments. She hopes to go to Midwestern State in the fall. Maddie found her love for cheer in 3rd grade in LCFCA, then moved on to competitive cheer and middle school cheer. She was in high school cheer all 4 years and a Varsity Cheerleader since her sophomore year. Maddie has a huge heart, she is dedicated, and she’s also a hard worker. Maddie worked hard to maintain a strong GPA while she also worked on the weekends.She’s sad about not being able to say her good byes to all her friends and her teachers and about all the missed senior year traditions but she is showing such resilience and strength during this time. I can’t wait to see what the future holds for you, sweet Maddie. We love you to the moon and back💚💚

post_text:
LDHS Senior 2020 Spotlight – Zoe Brewer

Congratulations to my 2020 Lake Dallas Graduating Senior, Zoe Brewer♥️

You have been a shining star since your debut in 2002! You’ve always had a sincere smile and heart that everyone seems to gravitate to.

From your early days in Illinois at Holy Family elementary school, to North Ridge Middle School, to now...you’ve been a young lady of class and honor, one that has kept your eye on the prize, while always caring for others. I have been sad beyond words that you will not be performing in the Spring Show that you (and dozens more!) have worked so hard all year for. But, just remember: the destination is never as thrilling as the journey... and you, my love, have had quite a journey! Words cannot express my pride and confidence I have for you and your future ahead. Soar high, my beautiful butterfly 🦋

post_text:
LDHS Senior 2020 Spotlight – Maribella Barnett

Maribella Barnett (Bella) is a 13 year senior at LDHS. Early in her high school career she had to make a choice to stop being a goal keeper due to head injuries. She wanted to keep her brain in great shape to continue being the straight A student she was. She has always been very driven and it shows in her drive to get where she’s going! She will graduate with her CCMA license and will be on her way to TWU in the fall with lots of classes already under her belt.
She will be a nurse practitioner focusing on labor and delivery once she is done with her Masters.

We are so proud of her and can’t wait to see what good she does in this world. I hope she is able to keep the compassion in her heart and her wicked sense of humor for what the future holds for her ♥️

Congratulations Zach! Being his mom is amazing!

LDHS Senior 2020 Spotlight:

Lexi, I am so blessed to be your mom. You have made me so proud to see the young lady you have become. I know this year didn’t end as expected....but that’s your style ❤️

Lexi Maiwald has been a Falcon for 11 1/2 of her school years. She always worked hard and maintained As and Bs. She participated in PALS and has been a high school cheerleader for all 4 years. Sophomore year she was cheer captain for the JV team.

She has always had a passion and love for animals. Always wanting to bring home every stray. She started working 2 years ago as a kennel tech for Corinth Animal Hospital (on top of school and cheer) and has worked up to vet tech there. She’s loved by the vets there and always looking to learn more procedures and techniques. Lexi plans to attend Texas A&M for veterinary medicine degree in the future.

Congrats Lexi! You did it. We love you!

post_text:
LDHS Senior 2020 spotlight:
Jason Hardy, It has been a blessing watching you grow into a caring and hard working young man. Here are some of his favorites and accomplishments. Jason has enjoyed being in physics class and hanging out with friends. His greatest accomplishment was getting his welding certification before winter break. The thing he most admires about his family is their love for the Lord. During his free time he likes working with dogs and playing video games. While attending Lake Dallas his activities were Law club, Science club, Chess club and Football. Football was his favorite of course. We thoroughly enjoyed watching him play. Jason’s advice for the incoming Freshman is to enjoy your time here, it goes by fast. His plans after High School are to attend a trade school to achieve a hands on career. We are so excited to see what the future holds for this bright and loving young man. Mom & Dad

Elliott, The time has passed by far too quickly. We have savored every special moment as you have matured into the Godly young man you are today. You are already so accomplished, from your volunteer work with the non profit OLIE (one life is enough) by traveling to numerous Texas schools to help end distracted driving as well as traveling to south Texas to help serve hot meals to those impacted by Hurricane Harvey.

We are excited to watch you continue your passion for flying while attending Spartan College of Aeronautics and Aviation. We’re amazed by the love and excitement you have for your country by staying informed in the political realm!

We couldn’t be more proud of you! Much Love, Mom and Dad

Meal Service pickup will still be on Monday, April 13. Parents, please read the newsletter on Sunday evening for important information about an upcoming Meal Service change.

As Spring Break approaches, please know that we are monitoring the COVID-19 situation through the department of Health and Human Services and the Centers for Disease Control. We recognize the uncertainty and concern of everyone and ask that you help partner with us and concentrate on preventative measures.

At this time the District will adhere to the adopted calendar and schedule. Should any changes occur, we will communicate via a call out, emails, district website and social media accounts.

Thank you and have a safe Spring Break.

Click here for District COVID-19 information and communications: https://www.ldisd.net/site/Default.aspx?PageID=7294

post_text:
LDHS Update: Oct. 4 - 2:30 pm

We have increased police and administrative presence at LDHS and all information is being processed and taken seriously. Additionally, we are working very closely with law enforcement to ensure any potential threats or issues are diffused. Those involved in yesterday’s altercation have been removed. Student safety is our top priority.

We are not able to answer publicly all the questions being posed on Facebook at this time. If you would like to meet with the district to discuss your concerns, know that district representatives are available today if you would like to come to the high school campus. You can also e-mail ldpr@ldisd.net with any questions you may have.

Our goal is to ensure that you and your student feel safe in LDISD. We appreciate your willingness to partner with us. Thank you.
